premise_source_doc_sentence: Gaius Julius Caesar  (  -LSB- ˈɡaː.i.ʊs ˈjuː.li.ʊs ˈkae̯.sar -RSB- ; 13 July 100 BC -- 15 March 44 BC  )  , known as Julius Caesar , was a Roman politician , general , and notable author of Latin prose .
Julius Caesar  (  judge  )   (  1557/8 -- 1636  )  , an English judge and politician  (  MP for Reigate , Bletchingley , Windsor , Westminster , Middlesex and Maldon  )
Cajus Julius Caesar  (  born 1951  )  , German politician  (  CDU  )  , member of the German parliament , the Bundestag
